question:
Given the code snippet, what is the output? 

```java
class MyTask implements Runnable {
    public void run() {
        System.out.print("2");
    }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Thread t = new Thread(new MyTask());
        t.start();
        System.out.print("1");
    }
}
```

Consider the following code. How many threads are created and running concurrently (at the same time) when the main method is executed?

```java
public class AdvancedThreadTest {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Line 1: Main thread is running
        Runnable r = () -> {
            Thread t = Thread.currentThread();
            System.out.println(t.getName());
        };

        Thread t1 = new Thread(r, "Thread-A");
        Thread t2 = new Thread(r, "Thread-B");
        Thread t3 = new Thread(r);
        Thread t4 = new Thread(r);

        t1.start(); // Line 2
        t2.run();   // Line 3
        t3.start(); // Line 4
        t4.start(); // Line 5

        // Line 6
    }
}
```
